"""Setup script for {{name}}.

Runs at install time and via `toolbase setup {{name}}`. Handles
configuration that's too involved for the declarative `config:` block
in toolkit.yaml — for example: data downloads, hardware detection,
multi-step flows.

This file is a starting point. Delete what you don't need.

Two functions are recognized:

- `setup(ctx)` — interactive setup. Runs at `toolbase install` and
  on demand via `toolbase setup`. Free to prompt, download, write
  config, do arbitrary Python work.
- `validate(ctx)` — quick check called at every `toolbase serve`
  startup. Must be fast (target <100ms) — no prompts, no downloads,
  just config reads. Return False to refuse-to-serve with a clear
  message; the user fixes and re-runs.

`ctx` is a SetupContext. Full API:
https://tool-base.org/docs/configuration#setup-script
"""


def setup(ctx):
    """Interactive setup. Returning False (or raising) reports
    failure; install completes regardless, and the user is told to
    re-run via `toolbase setup {{name}}` after fixing the issue."""
    ctx.info("Setting up {{name}}...")

    # ── Read user input ─────────────────────────────────────────
    # All prompts honor --yes / --no / --no-input flags. In skip mode
    # they fall back to defaults (or None if no default is given).
